@startuml Simplified IMS-DC-SDK Flow Summary

title Simplified Flow: How Mini Apps Use Data Channels in 5G Calls

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor<<sdk>> LightBlue
    BorderColor<<sdk>> DarkBlue
    BackgroundColor<<miniapp>> LightGreen
    BorderColor<<miniapp>> DarkGreen
    BackgroundColor<<5g>> LightYellow
    BorderColor<<5g>> Orange
    BackgroundColor<<network>> LightCoral
    BorderColor<<network>> Red
}

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<sdk>> AliceBlue
    BorderColor<<sdk>> Blue
    BackgroundColor<<miniapp>> Honeydew
    BorderColor<<miniapp>> Green
    BackgroundColor<<5g>> LightYellow
    BorderColor<<5g>> Orange
}

' Main actors
actor "User A\n(Your Phone)" as UserA
actor "User B\n(Friend's Phone)" as UserB

' Layer 1: Mini App Layer
package "📱 MINI APP LAYER\n(What Users See & Interact With)" <<miniapp>> {
    component [Mini App UI\n(HTML5/JavaScript)\n\nExamples:\n- Share menu during call\n- Real-time translation\n- AR filters\n- Game overlay] as MiniApp <<miniapp>>

    note right of MiniApp
        **Mini Apps are like web pages**
        that run DURING phone calls.

        They can send data to the
        other person on the call.
    end note
}

' Layer 2: SDK Bridge
package "🔗 SDK BRIDGE\n(Connects Mini App to Phone's Hardware)" <<sdk>> {
    component [DSBridge\n\nTranslates JavaScript\ncalls to Android code] as Bridge <<sdk>>

    component [SDK Managers\n\n- DCManager: Creates data channels\n- MiniAppManager: Runs apps\n- CallManager: Monitors call] as Managers <<sdk>>
}

' Layer 3: Terminal/Modem (5G Hardware)
package "📡 TERMINAL LAYER\n(Your Phone's 5G Hardware)" <<5g>> {
    component [Modem/Chipset\n\nThe physical chip that\nconnects to 5G towers.\n\nHandles:\n✓ Voice call\n✓ Video call\n✓ Data channel (NEW!)] as Modem <<5g>>

    note right of Modem
        **Think of it like this:**

        Old calls = only voice/video

        5G New Calling = voice/video
        PLUS data channel for apps
    end note
}

' Layer 4: Network
package "☁️ 5G NETWORK\n(The Internet Infrastructure)" <<network>> {
    cloud "5G Towers &\nIMS Core Network\n\nRoutes your call and\ndata to the other person" as Network <<network>>

    note bottom of Network
        **IMS (IP Multimedia Subsystem)**
        is the technology that handles
        voice/video calls over 5G internet.

        This SDK adds DATA CHANNELS
        on top of those calls.
    end note
}

' Flow arrows with explanations

UserA --> MiniApp : 1. User taps\n"Send Menu"\nbutton

MiniApp --> Bridge : 2. Mini app calls:\n<b>createDataChannel()</b>\n(JavaScript function)

Bridge --> Managers : 3. SDK translates\nto Android code

Managers --> Modem : 4. SDK tells modem:\n"Create a data tunnel\nto the other phone"

Modem --> Network : 5. Modem sends\nrequest through\n5G network

Network --> Modem : 6. Network confirms\ndata channel created

Modem --> Managers : 7. Modem notifies:\n"Channel ready!"

Managers --> MiniApp : 8. SDK tells mini app:\n"You can send data now"

MiniApp --> Bridge : 9. User sends menu:\n<b>sendData(menu_json)</b>

Bridge --> Managers : 10. Forward data

Managers --> Modem : 11. Send through\ndata channel

Modem --> Network : 12. Transmit over 5G

Network --> UserB : 13. Delivered to\nfriend's phone

' Key concepts box
legend bottom
    |= Concept |= Simple Explanation |
    | **Mini App** | Web app (HTML/JS) that runs during a call. Like a browser tab, but for calls. |
    | **SDK (This Project)** | The software that lets mini apps talk to 5G hardware. Like a translator. |
    | **Data Channel** | A "tunnel" for sending data during a call (separate from voice/video). |
    | **Terminal/Modem** | The 5G chip in your phone. It talks to cell towers. |
    | **IMS Network** | Internet-based phone system. Handles calls over 5G data (not old cellular). |
    | **AIDL** | Android Interface Definition Language - how SDK talks to modem chip. |
end legend

' Additional explanation box
note as N1
<b><size:14>🎯 THE BIG PICTURE</size></b>

<b>Problem this SDK solves:</b>
During a regular phone call, you can only send voice/video.
What if you want to send OTHER data? (menu, game moves, AR data, etc.)

<b>Solution:</b>
1. Your phone is on a 5G call (voice + video flowing)
2. SDK creates a DATA CHANNEL (separate pipe for app data)
3. Mini app can now send JSON, files, game data, etc.
4. All happening DURING THE SAME CALL!

<b>Real-world example:</b>
• You call a restaurant
• During the call, a menu mini-app opens
• You tap items on the menu
• The data (your order) sends through DATA CHANNEL
• Restaurant sees your order in real-time
• You confirm verbally via VOICE CHANNEL
• All in one call!
end note

@enduml
